			<div><span><br><blockquote><hr>Burncrew187 wrote:<br>If you can't make in iksar without buying Kunark, and you can't make a Vah Shir without buying luclin, what makes you think you're going to be able to make a beserker and beastlord on start?<br><div></div><br><hr></blockquote>Iksar can't be made unless you start in Kunark.  Vah Shir can't be made unless you start in Luclin.<br><br>Dwarven, Barbarian, Ogre, and Troll Berserkers can start, and exist in the old world.  Barbarian, Troll, and Ogres can be Beastlords.  Add Dwarves to that and you've got the races that can be Berserkers.<br><br>Besides, race doesn't fundamentally change how you play your character (well, besides what your starting factions are).  Class, however, does.<br></span></div>	
