		<td rowspan=2 bgcolor="#050A0E" width=1><img src="/i/p.gif" height=1 width=1 border=0 alt=""><br></td>
	
		<td colspan=2 class="msg_text_cell" width="100%" valign=top style="text-align: justify; 
		" 
			>
			<DIV>Bazaar and PoK are now global in EQ... but will not be available on the progression server at start.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Having Beastlords and Berzerkers at start does not make any sense to me game play wise OR lore wise. </DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Beastlords would be unable to do their epic as it requires access to Luclin. It is also Luclin era loot with it's stats and procs. Also, lore wise I think of it this way. Beastlords were released as the same time as access to the moon was gained and we met with the Vah Shir. Until this time, the knowledge of the beastlord was loss to all races on Norrath and it was this event that allowed the lessons to be taught to the Norrathian races.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Berzerkers have an issue when it comes to their epic as well. While I believe it CAN be done with old world zones, it is a GoD era weapon, not a Kunark era weapon. Also, it adds mobs into zones that are a bit out of line at that point. Picture heading into PoFear and having Ireblind imp up when you are all level 50 in Original and Kunark era gear (either from a previous failed attempt or because you run to wall and kill scarlings and accidently kill the enraged)... It would like zoning up into Severilous, VS, Cazic, or Trak. Not something most guilds JUST getting into Fear at this point in the game could handle on zoning in. Also, Fear to the best of my knowledge will be one of the zones reverted back to original condition (as well as the mobs in Hate) and as such the mob would not be there in that condition.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>What I am trying to say is... there is a LOT more tied to opening up these classes at the start of the server then some people realize. I personally HOPE they will not be allowed as there are still game play and gear balance issues in the game due to the addition of these classes to EQ as a whole.</DIV>
								<p><div style="width: 100%; height: 120; overflow: hidden;">
								
							<a>Athiena : Angel of White Wind, Drinal</a>
							</div>
								
