<P>And yes, IMO, at this point if people don't have Luclin, there is little point in keeping them from making Beastlords, seeing as how new accounts sold in stores have had the Luclin expansion on them for years.&nbsp; And yes, IMO, at this point if people don't have Discord, there is little point in keeping them from making Berserkers, because though the length of time is different, new storebought accounts will include this expansion anyway.</P>
<P>And, there is a flaw in your logic of calling races and classes 'content' - by that logic, all gear and spells from an expansion are also 'content' yet people can use the tradeable gear and spells without owning the expansion.&nbsp; Ought that 'content' be locked away from people who lack the relevant expansion?</P>	
