<span style="font-size: 8pt; font-weight: normal;">
Reply <a href="/eq/board/message?board.id=Progression&message.id=15403#M15403">75</a> of 85
</span>

			<br><img src="/i/p.gif" width=1 height=6><br>
			<span style="font-size: 8pt; font-weight: normal;">
			
					Viewed 159 times<br>
					
			</span>
			
		</td>
		
		<td rowspan=2 bgcolor="#050A0E" width=1><img src="/i/p.gif" height=1 width=1 border=0 alt=""><br></td>
	
		<td colspan=2 class="msg_text_cell" width="100%" valign=top style="text-align: justify; 
		" 
			>
			<DIV></DIV><BR>
<BLOCKQUOTE>
<HR>
Ermentraud wrote:<BR>
<DIV></DIV><BR>
<BLOCKQUOTE>
<HR>
Astroshak wrote:<BR>
<DIV></DIV><BR>
<BLOCKQUOTE>
<HR>
--arkanis-- wrote:<BR>Maybe this is not a dev decision as much as an SoE decision.&nbsp; Those expansions were marketed so that if you purchased that expasnion, you got the reward of another race.&nbsp; If they unlock the classes, should they also unlock the 9th spell slot?&nbsp; Because that's also tied to an expansion. Maybe this is unbelievable to you, but there are players that do NOT own the expansions past PoP.&nbsp; Should those people have access to Beserkers?&nbsp; <BR><BR>It's progression, you are meant to go through the content as it was originally presented.&nbsp; Here's a newsflash, races and classes are also considered 'content'. <BR><BR>Tanoril <BR>
<DIV></DIV><BR>
<HR>
</BLOCKQUOTE>
<P>We're not talking about races, we're talking about classes.&nbsp; The ninth spell slot is a non-issue, as it is unlocked via AA, not an automatic thing from just posessing an expansion.&nbsp; </P>
<P>And yes, IMO, at this point if people don't have Luclin, there is little point in keeping them from making Beastlords, seeing as how new accounts sold in stores have had the Luclin expansion on them for years.&nbsp; And yes, IMO, at this point if people don't have Discord, there is little point in keeping them from making Berserkers, because though the length of time is different, new storebought accounts will include this expansion anyway.</P>
<P><STRONG>And, there is a flaw in your logic of calling races and classes 'content' - by that logic, all gear and spells from an expansion are also 'content' <U>yet people can use the tradeable gear and spells without owning the expansion.&nbsp; Ought that 'content' be locked away from people who lack the relevant expansion?</U></STRONG></P><BR>
<HR>
</BLOCKQUOTE>OK I must interject, this is a PROGRESSION SERVER, this statement makes no sense here.&nbsp; &nbsp;Do you want to know why???<BR>On this server, i can't use the gear from Luclin for example on Vellious content, until the expansion is unlocked.&nbsp;Meaning I don't have the expansion.&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Why is this so hard for&nbsp;people to comprehend?&nbsp; The devs have spoken, and unfortunately their answer is No, no amount of begging, and complaining is going to change it.&nbsp; It can't be done, accept it, and move on.<BR>
<HR>
</BLOCKQUOTE>
<P><BR>The statement makes perfect sense, when you consider the servers in general.&nbsp; The request is to make these two classes global, no longer tied to an expansion, in order to fulfill one of the "mission statements" of this server : for everyone to start on an equal footing.&nbsp; If they are made global, however, it would apply to all servers, not just the Progression Server.&nbsp; Also, if someone does not have Luclin then when Luclin is unlocked on the Progression Server, they won't be able to access the moon, but will be able to access 'content' from Luclin : tradeable spells, and gear.</P>
<P>&nbsp;</P>
<P>And yes, it could be done, <EM><U>IF</U></EM> they chose to.&nbsp; The arguments for it are putting these two classes on an equal footing with everyone else : playable at start, the vast majority of players (&gt; 99%) on other servers have these two expansions and so wouldn't be affected by making them global, and there would be just as much work with recoding mobs and mob drops in making them availalbe from day one as there would be in preventing class specific drops from those two classes from dropping before those two classes are unlocked.&nbsp; So no, I don't have to accept their decision on this issue - it wouldn't be the first decision they've rethought and changed their minds on, y'know.</P>
<P>Oh, and to the person who posted after Ermentraud, who I didn't quote : Berserkers came out with the Gates of Discord expansion, not Omens of War.</P>	
